Introduction

API documentation for Al-Yaseen ERP Project Management and Inventory Management modules.

Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000/ 
Welcome to the Al-Yaseen ERP API documentation for Project Management and Inventory Management modules. This API provides comprehensive endpoints for:

## Project Management Module
- **Projects**: Complete project lifecycle management with CRUD operations, search, and filtering
- **Tasks**: Task management with assignments, priorities, and status tracking
- **Milestones**: Project milestone tracking and management
- **Resources**: Resource allocation and management with supplier integration
- **Documents**: Project document management and file handling
- **Project Financials**: Financial tracking and budget management
- **Project Risks**: Risk assessment and management

## Inventory Management Module
- **Inventory Items**: Complete inventory item management with stock tracking
- **Warehouses**: Multi-warehouse management and operations
- **Stock Movements**: Stock transfer and movement tracking
- **Items**: Advanced item management with categories and specifications
- **Units**: Unit of measure management and conversions
- **BOM (Bill of Materials)**: Product structure and component management
- **Barcode Management**: Barcode types and scanning integration

All endpoints require authentication using Laravel Sanctum tokens unless otherwise specified.

<aside>As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile).
You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).</aside>

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

Endpoints

POST api/v1/auth/login

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/auth/login" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/auth/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Inventory Management / BOM Items

APIs for managing Bill of Materials (BOM) items, including component relationships and requirements calculation.

Get BOM items for a specific item (Bill of Materials).

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/item/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/item/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Calculate material requirements for production.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/calculate-requirements" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"item_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"production_quantity\": 45
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/calculate-requirements"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "item_id": "consequatur",
    "production_quantity": 45
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/bom-items/calculate-requirements

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

item_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the items table. Example: consequatur

production_quantity   number   

Must be at least 0.01. Example: 45

Update the specified BOM item.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"item_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"component_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"unit_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"quantity\": 45
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/bom-items/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "item_id": "consequatur",
    "component_id": "consequatur",
    "unit_id": "consequatur",
    "quantity": 45
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

PUT api/v1/bom-items/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the bom item. Example: consequatur

Body Parameters

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

item_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the items table. Example: consequatur

component_id   string   

The value and item_id must be different. The id of an existing record in the items table. Example: consequatur

unit_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the units table. Example: consequatur

quantity   number   

Must be at least 0.000001. Example: 45

    --header "Accept: application/json"

);

Body Parameters

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

unit_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the units table. Example: consequatur

parent_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the items table.

item_number   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

code   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq

catalog_number   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: xbajwbpilpmufinllwloa

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: uydlsmsjuryvojcybzvrb

description   string  optional  

Example: Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.

model   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: dtdsufvyvddqamniihfqc

unit_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: oynlazghdtqtqxbajwbpi

type   string   

Example: raw_material

Must be one of:
  • product
  • service
  • material
  • raw_material
quantity   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 41

balance   number  optional  

Example: 11613.31890586

minimum_limit   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 50

maximum_limit   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 55

reorder_limit   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 19

max_reorder_limit   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 70

first_purchase_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 70

second_purchase_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 12

third_purchase_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 66

purchase_discount_rate   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 4

purchase_prices_include_vat   boolean  optional  

Example: true

first_sale_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 65

second_sale_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 72

third_sale_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 18

sale_discount_rate   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 21

maximum_sale_discount_rate   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 24

minimum_allowed_sale_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 76

sale_prices_include_vat   boolean  optional  

Example: false

item_subject_to_vat   boolean  optional  

Example: false

notes   string  optional  

Example: consequatur

barcode   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

barcode_type   string  optional  

Example: C128

Must be one of:
  • C128
  • EAN13
  • C39
  • UPCA
  • ITF
expiry_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after today. Example: 2106-10-15

image   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

color   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: xbajwbpilpmufinllwloa

Example: false

Update the specified document.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/documents/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "title=vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq"\
    --form "project_number=amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt"\
    --form "project_name=qxbajwbpilpmufinllwlo"\
    --form "description=Et a qui ducimus."\
    --form "document_category=drawing"\
    --form "status=active"\
    --form "upload_date=2025-09-16T10:25:38"\
    --form "version=smsjuryvojcybzvrb"\
    --form "file=@C:\Users\TSC\AppData\Local\Temp\php8EC9.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/documents/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('title', 'vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq');
body.append('project_number', 'amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt');
body.append('project_name', 'qxbajwbpilpmufinllwlo');
body.append('description', 'Et a qui ducimus.');
body.append('document_category', 'drawing');
body.append('status', 'active');
body.append('upload_date', '2025-09-16T10:25:38');
body.append('version', 'smsjuryvojcybzvrb');
body.append('file', document.querySelector('input[name="file"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Update the specified project financial.

requires authentication

Example request:

    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/project-financials/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"exchange_rate\": 21,
    \"reference_type\": \"mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa\",
    \"reference_id\": \"mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq\",
    \"amount\": 23,
    \"date\": \"2025-09-16T10:25:39\",
    \"description\": \"Aut consequatur debitis et.\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/project-financials/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "exchange_rate": 21,
    "reference_type": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",
    "reference_id": "mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq",
    "amount": 23,
    "date": "2025-09-16T10:25:39",
    "description": "Aut consequatur debitis et."
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

URL Parameters

Body Parameters

The id of an existing record in the projects table.

currency_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the currencies table.

exchange_rate   number  optional  

Must be at least 0.0001. Must not be greater than 999999.9999. Example: 21

reference_type   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

reference_id   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq

amount   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 999999999999.99. Example: 23

date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-16T10:25:39

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: Aut consequatur debitis et.

updated_by   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

Update the specified milestone.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/milestones/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq\",
    \"start_date\": \"2025-09-16T10:25:38\",
    \"status\": \"in_progress\",
    \"milestone_number\": 2,
    \"description\": \"Molestias ipsam sit veniam sed fuga aspernatur.\",
    \"end_date\": \"2106-10-15\",
    \"progress\": 13,
    \"notes\": \"qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/milestones/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq",
    "start_date": "2025-09-16T10:25:38",
    "status": "in_progress",
    "milestone_number": 2,
    "description": "Molestias ipsam sit veniam sed fuga aspernatur.",
    "end_date": "2106-10-15",
    "progress": 13,
    "notes": "qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

PUT api/v1/milestones/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the milestone. Example: consequatur

Body Parameters

project_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the projects table.

name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq

start_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-16T10:25:38

status   string  optional  

Example: in_progress

Must be one of:
  • not_started
  • in_progress
  • completed
milestone_number   integer  optional  

Must be at least 1. Example: 2

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: Molestias ipsam sit veniam sed fuga aspernatur.

end_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to start_date. Example: 2106-10-15

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 13

notes   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 2000 characters. Example: qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam

    \"project_value\": 12,
    \"project_manager_name\": \"tdsufvyvddqamniihfqco\",

    \"end_date\": \"2106-10-15\",
    \"status\": \"closed\",
    \"notes\": \"consequatur\",
    \"customer_name\": \"mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa\",
    \"customer_email\": \"eloisa.harber@example.com\",
    \"customer_phone\": \"fqcoynlazghdtqtqx\",
    \"licensed_operator\": \"bajwbpilpmufinllwloau\",
    \"budget\": 87,
    \"actual_cost\": 13,
    \"progress\": 12
}"

    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/projects/consequatur"
);

    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "currency_price": 73,
    "include_vat": true,
    "project_number": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",

    "project_value": 12,

    "customer_name": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",

Request      

PUT api/v1/projects/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the project. Example: consequatur

Body Parameters

company_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the companies table.

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

fiscal_year_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the fiscal_years table.

cost_center_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the cost_centers table.

customer_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the customers table.

currency_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the currencies table.

currency_price   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 73

include_vat   boolean  optional  

Example: true

project_number   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq

description   string  optional  

Example: Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.

project_value   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 12

manager_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

project_manager_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: tdsufvyvddqamniihfqco

start_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-16T10:25:37

end_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after start_date. Example: 2106-10-15

status   string  optional  

Example: closed

Must be one of:
  • draft
  • open
  • on-hold
  • cancelled
  • closed
country_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the countries table.

notes   string  optional  

Example: consequatur

customer_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

customer_email   string  optional  

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: eloisa.harber@example.com

customer_phone   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 20 characters. Example: fqcoynlazghdtqtqx

licensed_operator   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: bajwbpilpmufinllwloau

budget   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 87

actual_cost   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 13

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 12

Update the specified resource.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/resources/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"role\": \"vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq\",
    \"resource_type\": \"supplier\",
    \"supplier_number\": \"amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt\",
    \"supplier_name\": \"qxbajwbpilpmufinllwlo\",
    \"project_number\": \"auydlsmsjuryvojcybzvr\",
    \"project_name\": \"byickznkygloigmkwxphl\",
    \"allocation_percentage\": 22,
    \"allocation_value\": 0,
    \"notes\": \"zjrcnfbaqywuxhgjjmzux\",
    \"status\": \"inactive\",
    \"allocation\": \"jubqouzswiwxtrkimfcat\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/resources/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "role": "vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq",
    "resource_type": "supplier",
    "supplier_number": "amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt",
    "supplier_name": "qxbajwbpilpmufinllwlo",
    "project_number": "auydlsmsjuryvojcybzvr",
    "project_name": "byickznkygloigmkwxphl",
    "allocation_percentage": 22,
    "allocation_value": 0,
    "notes": "zjrcnfbaqywuxhgjjmzux",
    "status": "inactive",
    "allocation": "jubqouzswiwxtrkimfcat"
};

    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

PUT api/v1/resources/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the resource. Example: consequatur

Body Parameters

project_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the projects table.

supplier_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the suppliers table.

role   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq

resource_type   string  optional  

Example: supplier

Must be one of:
  • supplier
  • internal
  • contractor
  • consultant
supplier_number   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 100 characters. Example: amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt

supplier_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: qxbajwbpilpmufinllwlo

project_number   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 100 characters. Example: auydlsmsjuryvojcybzvr

project_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: byickznkygloigmkwxphl

allocation_percentage   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 22

allocation_value   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 0

notes   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 2000 characters. Example: zjrcnfbaqywuxhgjjmzux

status   string  optional  

Example: inactive

Must be one of:
  • active
  • inactive
  • completed
allocation   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 500 characters. Example: jubqouzswiwxtrkimfcat

Update the specified task.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/tasks/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"task_name\": \"vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq\",
    \"due_date\": \"2025-09-16T10:25:38\",
    \"status\": \"done\",
    \"title\": \"amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt\",
    \"description\": \"Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.\",
    \"notes\": \"consequatur\",
    \"priority\": \"high\",
    \"start_date\": \"2025-09-16T10:25:38\",
    \"estimated_hours\": 13,
    \"actual_hours\": 16,
    \"progress\": 5,
    \"records\": [
        \"opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni\"
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/tasks/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "task_name": "vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq",
    "due_date": "2025-09-16T10:25:38",
    "status": "done",
    "title": "amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt",
    "description": "Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.",
    "notes": "consequatur",
    "priority": "high",
    "start_date": "2025-09-16T10:25:38",
    "estimated_hours": 13,
    "actual_hours": 16,
    "progress": 5,
    "records": [
        "opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni"
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

PUT api/v1/tasks/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the task. Example: consequatur

Body Parameters

project_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the projects table.

task_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq

assigned_to   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the employees table.

due_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-16T10:25:38

status   string  optional  

Example: done

Must be one of:
  • to_do
  • in_progress
  • done
  • blocked
milestone_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the project_milestones table.

title   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt

description   string  optional  

Example: Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.

notes   string  optional  

Example: consequatur

priority   string  optional  

Example: high

Must be one of:
  • low
  • medium
  • high
  • urgent
start_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-16T10:25:38

estimated_hours   integer  optional  

Must be at least 1. Must not be greater than 1000. Example: 13

actual_hours   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 1000. Example: 16

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 5

records   string[]  optional  

Must be a valid URL. Must not be greater than 500 characters.
